entry.title: Rubber Johnny (Aphex Twin Musicvideo)
entry.content: Rubber Johnny is a 6 minute experimental short film and music video directed by Chris Cunningham in 2005, using music composed by Aphex Twin. The concept for Rubber Johnny came from Cunningham imagining a raver morphing as he danced. The idea evolved to the present film, in which Johnny (played by Cunningham) is an isolated mutant child with a huge overgrown cranium, strapped into a wheelchair and locked in a basement. Capable of morphing his body, he spends his life trying to amuse himself and his dog, a terrified chihuahua.

entry.title: Aphex Twin - Alberto Balsalm
entry.content: Another Aphex Twin track that I've yet to see uploaded besides small clips or covers, so here's the original for you guys. I love it because it's got an almost haunting sound to it. It's really stuck with me, despite all of his other work I've heard. Track info: Title: Alberto Balsalm Artist: Aphex Twin Album: ...I Care Because You Do [90-94] I do not take credit for making the image, or the music. Both of which are to Aphex Twin and his label, Rephlex Records/Warp Records.
